ElementDescription: Has your child ever received any of the following services? Speech-language therapy (services provided by a licensed speech-language pathologist to help a child with speech, language, communication, social interaction, and/or feeding skills)

Has your child ever received any of the following services? Occupational therapy (services provided by a licensed occupational therapist to help the child function better in daily life, including participating in play, self-care (toileting, feeding, dressing, etc.), and family routines)

Has your child ever received any of the following services? Physical therapy (services provided by a licensed physical therapist to help a child with the movement (or motor) skills needed for different activities)

Has your child ever received any of the following services? Infant Toddler Services (services occur in your home and may include visits from multiple providers (speech-language pathologist, occupational therapist, etc.))

Has your child ever received any of the following services? Developmental therapy (services provided by a child development specialist to help a child develop skills in a variety of areas, including cognition, and social interaction)

Has your child ever received any of the following services? Other therapy (e.g., Applied Behavior Analysis (ABA), Developmental, Individual difference Relationship-Based Therapy (DIR), Relationship Developmental Intervention Therapy (RDI), counseling or psychological services, social skills training, etc.)
Indicate type of therapy or services assessed
Notes: 1=Speech language therapy; 2=Occupational therapy; 3=Physical therapy; 4=Infant toddler services; 5=Developmental therapy; 6=Other
